        "taskDescription": [
            "Suppose a town of 5000 people is extremely unhappy with the country’s government.   Every day, there are about 500 meetings where two people discuss politics and their dissatisfaction with government.  A single terrorist comes to town with such a compelling message that every time he talks with another person, that person becomes a terrorist as well.  Moreover, the new terrorists have the same message, so they can recruit others.  Construct a model that shows how the number of terrorist and non-terrorists changes over the days.  You should assume that the two people who meet are randomly chosen from the population of 5001 individuals. "
        ],
